$ Oracle PL/SQL: wait (sleep) for the given amount of time with DBMS_LOCK.SLEEP

Executing `dbms_lock.sleep(secs)` makes the session wait for `secs` seconds.

gh|oracle-patterns|/Installed/dbms/lock/sleep.sql||

sa:

 `→ development/databases/Oracle/installed/packages/dbms/session[dbms_session].sleep`

  → development/databases/Oracle/installed/packages/dbms/lock

  The → development/databases/SQL-Server[SQL Server] equivalent of `dbms_lock.sleep` seems to be
  → development/databases/SQL-Server/T-SQL/statements/waitfor/delay[`waitfor delay …`].
